         <abstract id="aspace_d6bccfd4554b10d12cc481cebb4ca5b7">The Alumni files contain information about graduates of Andover Newton Theological School and its predecessors, Andover Theological Seminary and Newton Theological Institution.</abstract>
    
         <origination label="creator">
            <corpname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n82069857" source="naf">
               <part>Andover Newton Theological School</part>
            </corpname>
         </origination>
      </did>
      <arrangement id="aspace_110857b980b5f7adb42685e480254c73">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The files are primarily arranged by year of graduation and alphabetically within each year. The second series contains files that do not relate to specific years.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <bioghist id="aspace_d66494f1813edccba9564ecbcd63b930">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Andover Newton Theological School was established in 1965 by the merger of Andover Theological Seminary (established 1807) and Newton Theological Institution (established 1825). While maintaining a campus in Newton through 2018 and granting degrees through 2019, it formally affiliated with Yale Divinity School in 2017 and established a presence in New Haven as Andover Newton Seminary at Yale Divinity School.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_64e9106ec3246b8575e2449c75e24e38">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_0cde77aafb49f883f4bb9db90e7819c3">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>From the Andover Newton Theological School Collection, transferred to the Yale Divinity Library in 2017.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_d383b2cb870f5b6cc3aec2e173862a22">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Alumni files contain information about graduates of Andover Newton Theological School and its predecessors. This finding aid provides a rough guide to the years of graduation that are included in each box so that boxes can be retrieved from off-campus shelving for more specific investigation.  The finding aid will be refined to include all the names of alumni in the future, as time permits. The names provided indicate the first and last folder in each box, to assist with locating individuals when years of graduation may be spread across two boxes.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <prefercite id="aspace_3602c1bfd3011f82e6edf4ee3e549e90">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Andover Newton Theological School Alumni Files (RG 278), Special Collections, Yale Divinity School Library</p>  
      </prefercite>
